Kfar Silver (Hebrew: כְּפַר סִילְבֶר‎, lit. Silver Village) is a youth village in southern Israel. It contains a boarding school that teaches 200 pupils each year. the founder and first principal of the school was Author and Educator Aryeh Kotzer. Located near Ashkelon, the village falls under the jurisdiction of Hof Ashkelon Regional Council. In 2016 it had a population of 278.
